# Sample Rate Conversion Quality Identifiers

**API Collection**

Specifiers for sample rate conversion quality, used for the [doc://com.apple.audiotoolbox/documentation/AudioToolbox/kAudioConverterSampleRateConverterQuality] property.

## Overview

Higher-quality sample-rate conversions entail higher processing cost.

## Constants

- **kAudioConverterQuality_Max**: Specifies maximum sample-rate conversion quality.
- **kAudioConverterQuality_High**: Specifies high sample rate conversion quality.
- **kAudioConverterQuality_Medium**: Specifies medium sample rate conversion quality.
- **kAudioConverterQuality_Low**: Specifies low sample rate conversion quality.
- **kAudioConverterQuality_Min**: Specifies minimum sample rate conversion quality.

## Constants

- **Audio Converter Properties**: Audio converter properties, used with the [doc://com.apple.audiotoolbox/documentation/AudioToolbox/AudioConverterGetPropertyInfo(_:_:_:_:)], [doc://com.apple.audiotoolbox/documentation/AudioToolbox/AudioConverterGetProperty(_:_:_:_:)], and [doc://com.apple.audiotoolbox/documentation/AudioToolbox/AudioConverterSetProperty(_:_:_:_:)] functions.
- **Converter Priming Constants**: Constants used with the [doc://com.apple.audiotoolbox/documentation/AudioToolbox/kAudioConverterPrimeMethod] property.
- **Sample Rate Conversion Complexity Identifiers**: Specifiers for the sample rate conversion algorithm, used for the [doc://com.apple.audiotoolbox/documentation/AudioToolbox/kAudioConverterSampleRateConverterComplexity] property.
